org.microtitan.diffusive.cache

Class FifoCache<K,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microtitan.diffusive.cache.FifoCache<K,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Cache entry object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cache<K,T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FifoResultsCache

    public class FifoCache<K,T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cache<K,T>
    Cache that holds a maximum specified elements. When the maximum number of elements is exceeded, then the cache removes the oldest element. In other words, this is first-in, first-out (FIFO) cache.
    Author:
    Robert Philipp

    • Constructor Detail

      • FifoCache

        public FifoCache(int maxResults)
        Constructs a basic cache that holds the specified number of entries. When an item is added, and that causes the number of items to exceed the maximum number of items, the oldest item is dropped.
        Parameters:
        maxResults - The maximum number of cache entries allowed.

      • FifoCache

        public FifoCache()
        Constructs a basic cache that holds the default number of entries. When an item is added, and that causes the number of items to exceed the maximum number of items, the oldest item is dropped. The maximum number of cached items (MAX_ITEMS) defaults to a value of 100.
